==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cero
<hw>Ce"ro</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corrupt. fr. Sp.
<ets>sierra</ets> saw, sawfish, cero.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
large and valuable fish of the Mackerel family, of the genus
<gen>Scomberomorus</gen>. Two species are found in the West Indies and
less commonly on the Atlantic coast of the United States, -- the common
cero (<spn>Scomberomorus cavalla</spn>), called also
<altname>kingfish</altname>, and spotted, or king, cero
(<spn>Scomberomorus regalis</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cerograph</ent>⟦br⟧
